Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @Zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.
Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, half the
@Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), a pinch of @Salt{pinch},
and @Pepper{pinch}. Roast on top rack until tender and lightly browned,
~{14-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a large pan over
medium heat. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring constantly,
until golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{} and stir in a pinch of salt,
pepper, and as much lemon zest as you like. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in pan used for panko over medium heat. Add
@Orzo Pasta{8%ounce} and cook, stirring, until orzo is toasted and golden,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Vidalia Onion Paste{1/2%ounce}, remaining garlic powder, and @Water{2%cups}
(4 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Simmer,
stirring occasionally, until orzo is al dente, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid
has reduced and orzotto is creamy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in half the roasted zucchini and @Butter{1%tbsp}
(2 TBSP for 4). Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> TIP: Orzotto should be the consistency of risotto! If it seems too thick,
> stir in a splash of water.

== Lemony Arugula Salad ==

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp},
juice from one lemon wedge, a pinch of @Salt{pinch}, and @Pepper{pinch}
(for 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, 1 tsp sugar, and juice from two lemon wedges).

Add @Arugula{2%ounce} and @Sliced Almonds{1/2%ounce}; toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Divide orzotto between shallow bowls; divide salad between separate bowls.
Top orzotto with remaining roasted zucchini and panko. Serve with remaining
lemon wedges on the side.